results.name: Number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace 0 and subtrace 1.
comment: Let x = RootOf( z^2+z+1 ) and y = 1+x. Also the number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace 0 and subtrace x. Also the number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace 0 and subtrace y.
link: F. Ruskey, 4-ary Lyndon words with given trace and subtrace over GF(4)
example: a(4;0,1)=2 since the two 4-ary Lyndon words of trace 0, subtrace 1 and length 4 are { 0011, 11xx }, where x = RootOf( z^2+z+1 ).
results.author: _Frank Ruskey_ and Nate Kube, Aug 23 2002
